## What's in this folder

```
grant-finder/
├── api/
│   └── claude.js        ← Proxy function (calls Anthropic, keeps key secret)
├── public/
│   └── index.html       ← The Grant Finder UI (paste this into SurveyJS)
├── vercel.json          ← Vercel config
├── package.json         ← Project metadata
└── DEPLOY.md            ← This file
```

---

## Step 1 — Push to GitHub

1. Go to github.com and create a new repository (e.g. `grant-finder-proxy`)
2. Upload all files in this folder to the repository
   - Easiest way: drag and drop the files into the GitHub web interface
   - Make sure the folder structure is preserved (api/claude.js, public/index.html, etc.)

---

## Step 2 — Deploy to Vercel

1. Go to vercel.com and sign in (or create a free account)
2. Click **Add New Project**
3. Select **Import Git Repository** and choose your `grant-finder-proxy` repo
4. Click **Deploy** — Vercel will auto-detect the config from vercel.json

---

## Step 3 — Add your Anthropic API key

1. In your Vercel project dashboard, go to **Settings → Environment Variables**
2. Add a new variable:
   - **Name:** `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`
   - **Value:** your Anthropic API key (sk-ant-...)
   - **Environment:** Production, Preview, Development (tick all three)
3. Click **Save**
4. Go to **Deployments** and click **Redeploy** on your latest deployment
   (environment variables only take effect after a redeploy)

---

## Step 4 — Get your proxy URL

After deploying, your proxy URL will be:

```
https://YOUR-PROJECT-NAME.vercel.app/api/claude
```

You can find your project name in the Vercel dashboard URL or on the project overview page.

---

## Step 5 — Update the HTML

Open `public/index.html` and find this line near the top of the script:

```javascript
const PROXY_URL = 'https://YOUR-PROJECT.vercel.app/api/claude';
```

Replace `YOUR-PROJECT` with your actual Vercel project name. Save the file.

---

## Step 6 — Paste into SurveyJS

Copy the entire contents of `public/index.html` and paste it into the
SurveyJS HTML question markdown box.

The agent will start automatically — no API key prompt, no gate screen.

---

## Testing the proxy directly

You can test that the proxy is working by opening your browser console and running:

```javascript
fetch('https://YOUR-PROJECT.vercel.app/api/claude', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    model: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514',
    max_tokens: 50,
    messages: [{ role: 'user', content: 'Say hello' }]
  })
}).then(r => r.json()).then(console.log)
```

If you see a response with `content`, the proxy is working correctly.

---

## Troubleshooting

| Problem | Fix |
|---|---|
| Proxy returns 500 "API key not configured" | Re-check env variable name is exactly `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` and redeploy |
| Proxy returns CORS error | Check vercel.json is in the root of your repo |
| Agent doesn't start in SurveyJS | Make sure PROXY_URL in the HTML matches your actual Vercel URL |
| Vercel says "No framework detected" | That's fine — click Deploy anyway, it will work |
